s=\"token number\">20</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">;; change to `1` (true) to get the first value (`10`)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">i32<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>const</span> <span class=\"token number\">0</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">select</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Instruction</th>\n      <th>Binary opcode</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>select</code></td>\n      <td><code>0x1b</code></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><code>select t</code></td>\n      <td><code>0x1c</code></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"}],"summary":"The select instruction, selects one of its first two operands based on whether its third operand is zero or not. It shares some similarities with the ternary operator in other languages (e.g. false ? 10 : 20), but doesn't short-circuit.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-05-06T11:44:55.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/webassembly/reference/control_flow/select","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/webassembly/reference/control_flow/select/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/551e127a806da06cef89690863ccd21a596fb6ae","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/WebAssembly","title":"WebAssembly"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/WebAssembly/Reference","title":"WebAssembly instructions"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/WebAssembly/Reference/Control_flow","title":"WebAssembly control flow instructions"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/WebAssembly/Reference/Control_flow/Select","title":"Select"}],"pageTitle":"Select - WebAssembly | MDN","noIndexing":false}}